<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=673&amp;p=5886#p5886"><![CDATA[
If you have several games that use the same board hardware and are the same ROM size, you can put them on one pair of EPROM chips and use switches to control the upper address lines in order to select a game upon power-up.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Oct 25, 2005 11:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
