<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=673&amp;p=5686#p5686"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[NES Cartridge Combos]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=673&amp;p=5686#p5686"><![CDATA[
You can only put games that use the same mapper and games that use trivial mappers (e.g. NROM) in the same cart. You'll want to somehow add a second mapper that controls the upper address lines while the cart's own mapper controls the lower address lines.<br /><br />And have you considered developing your own NES software too?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Oct 20, 2005 3:28 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
